cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "DACS: Dynamic Attentional Context Scoping"
abstract: >
  Research prototype and preprint for Dynamic Attentional Context Scoping (DACS),
  a mechanism where a multi-agent orchestrator enters agent-triggered focus sessions
  to isolate per-agent context during steering interactions. Evaluated across 4 phases
  and 200 trials; DACS achieves 90-98% steering accuracy versus 21-60% for a flat-context
  baseline.
